---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="LMLAS — Longitudinal Mathematics Learning Analytics Study | ACLEDS"
  description="The Longitudinal Mathematics Learning Analytics Study: ACLEDS flagship research project tracking mathematics confidence and achievement across African schools."
>
  <section class="page-hero section-dark">
    <div class="container">
      <a href="/projects" class="back-link">← All Projects</a>
      <div class="hero-tags">
        <span class="tag tag-gold">Flagship Study</span>
        <span class="project-status active">Active</span>
      </div>
      <h1>Longitudinal Mathematics Learning Analytics Study</h1>
      <p class="project-mono">LMLAS · 2026 — ongoing</p>
      <p class="page-hero-sub">
        A multi-year tracking study examining how mathematics confidence,
        identity, and achievement co-evolve across primary and secondary
        schooling — using learning analytics methods to surface patterns
        invisible to cross-sectional research.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Quick facts bar -->
  <div class="facts-bar">
    <div class="container facts-inner">
      <div class="fact-item">
        <span class="fact-label">Design</span>
        <span class="fact-val">Longitudinal, mixed methods</span>
      </div>
      <div class="fact-divider"></div>
      <div class="fact-item">
        <span class="fact-label">Duration</span>
        <span class="fact-val">Multi-year</span>
      </div>
      <div class="fact-divider"></div>
      <div class="fact-item">
        <span class="fact-label">Status</span>
        <span class="fact-val">Data collection ongoing</span>
      </div>
      <div class="fact-divider"></div>
      <div class="fact-item">
        <span class="fact-label">PI</span>
        <span class="fact-val">Prosper Ablordeppey</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="project-layout">
        <!-- Main content -->
        <article class="project-body">
          <div class="body-section">
            <p class="eyebrow">Background</p>
            <h2>Why This Study?</h2>
            <div class="divider"></div>
            <p>
              Mathematics performance in African school systems has been a
              persistent policy concern. But most of the research on mathematics
              learning — even research conducted in Africa — is cross-sectional:
              it takes a snapshot at one moment in time, compares groups, and
              draws conclusions. What it cannot do is track how individual
              learners change over time.
            </p>
            <p>
              The LMLAS was designed to address this gap directly. By following
              cohorts of learners over multiple years, we can observe not just
              where students end up, but how they get there — and what factors
              along the way accelerate, sustain, or derail mathematics learning.
            </p>
            <p>
              The study is grounded in the insight that mathematics confidence
              and achievement are intertwined but distinct. Students can have
              high confidence and low achievement, or vice versa. The
              relationship between them shifts over time in patterned ways that
              have significant implications for teaching and curriculum design.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="body-section">
            <p class="eyebrow">Research Questions</p>
            <h2>What We Are Investigating</h2>
            <div class="divider"></div>
            <ol class="rq-list">
              <li>
                <span class="rq-num">RQ1</span>
                <div>
                  <strong>Confidence–Achievement Trajectories</strong>
                  <p>
                    How do mathematics confidence and measurable achievement
                    co-evolve across the primary school years, and in what ways
                    do they diverge?
                  </p>
                </div>
              </li>
              <li>
                <span class="rq-num">RQ2</span>
                <div>
                  <strong>Predictors of Positive Trajectories</strong>
                  <p>
                    What learner, teacher, classroom, and school-level factors
                    predict positive mathematics learning trajectories over
                    time?
                  </p>
                </div>
              </li>
              <li>
                <span class="rq-num">RQ3</span>
                <div>
                  <strong>Mathematical Identity</strong>
                  <p>
                    How does mathematical identity — the degree to which
                    students see themselves as "maths people" — interact with
                    achievement outcomes over time?
                  </p>
                </div>
              </li>
              <li>
                <span class="rq-num">RQ4</span>
                <div>
                  <strong>Analytics Advantage</strong>
                  <p>
                    What do learning analytics approaches reveal about
                    mathematics learning that traditional assessment data alone
                    cannot capture?
                  </p>
                </div>
              </li>
            </ol>
          </div>

          <div class="body-section">
            <p class="eyebrow">Approach</p>
            <h2>Methodology</h2>
            <div class="divider"></div>
            <p>
              The LMLAS uses a mixed-methods longitudinal design, combining:
            </p>
            <div class="method-grid">
              <div class="method-card">
                <h4>Standardised Assessments</h4>
                <p>
                  Validated mathematics assessments administered annually to
                  track achievement over time.
                </p>
              </div>
              <div class="method-card">
                <h4>Learner Surveys</h4>
                <p>
                  Annual surveys measuring confidence, identity, engagement, and
                  attitudes toward mathematics.
                </p>
              </div>
              <div class="method-card">
                <h4>Teacher Observations</h4>
                <p>
                  Structured classroom observations to capture pedagogical
                  practice and learning environment quality.
                </p>
              </div>
              <div class="method-card">
                <h4>Administrative Data</h4>
                <p>
                  School-level and system-level data including attendance,
                  progression, and national assessment results.
                </p>
              </div>
              <div class="method-card">
                <h4>Qualitative Interviews</h4>
                <p>
                  In-depth interviews with selected learners and teachers to
                  surface meanings and experiences.
                </p>
              </div>
              <div class="method-card">
                <h4>Learning Analytics</h4>
                <p>
                  Computational analysis of longitudinal datasets to identify
                  trajectory patterns and predictive factors.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="body-section">
            <p class="eyebrow">Implications</p>
            <h2>Why It Matters</h2>
            <div class="divider"></div>
            <p>
              The LMLAS is designed from the outset to produce findings that can
              reach policy and practice — not just academic literature. Key
              implications we anticipate include:
            </p>
            <ul class="implications-list">
              <li>
                Evidence to inform early identification of learners at risk of
                mathematics disengagement
              </li>
              <li>
                Insights for teacher professional development focused on
                confidence-building
              </li>
              <li>
                Recommendations for curriculum sequencing based on longitudinal
                trajectory data
              </li>
              <li>
                A replicable methodological model for longitudinal learning
                research in African school contexts
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </article>

        <!-- Sidebar -->
        <aside class="project-sidebar">
          <div class="card sidebar-card">
            <p class="eyebrow">Related Publications</p>
            <div class="sidebar-pubs">
              <div class="sidebar-pub">
                <span class="tag tag-gold" style="font-size:0.65rem"
                  >Working Paper</span
                >
                <p>
                  Mathematics Confidence and Achievement: A Longitudinal
                  Perspective
                </p>
                <span class="pub-author">Grace Amackson · 2025</span>
                <a href="/publications" class="pub-link-sm">Read →</a>
              </div>
            </div>
            <a
              href="/publications"
              class="btn btn-dark btn-sm"
              style="width:100%; justify-content:center; margin-top:1.25rem"
              >All Publications</a
            >
          </div>

          <div class="card sidebar-card" style="margin-top:1.5rem">
            <p class="eyebrow">Interested in Partnering?</p>
            <p
              style="font-size:0.875rem; color:var(--text-muted); margin-top:0.5rem"
            >
              Schools, researchers, and policy partners interested in connecting
              to this study are welcome to reach out.
            </p>
            <a
              href="/collaborate"
              class="btn btn-primary btn-sm"
              style="width:100%; justify-content:center; margin-top:1.25rem"
              >Enquire</a
            >
          </div>

          <div
            class="card sidebar-card"
            style="margin-top:1.5rem; background:var(--navy); border-color:rgba(200,151,58,0.2)"
          >
            <p class="eyebrow" style="color:var(--gold)">
              Principal Investigator
            </p>
            <div class="pi-block">
              <div class="pi-avatar"><span>GA</span></div>
              <div>
                <strong style="color:var(--white); font-family:var(--font-body)"
                  >Grace Amackson</strong
                >
                <p
                  style="font-size:0.78rem; color:rgba(232,237,244,0.6); margin-top:0.2rem"
                >
                  Founding Director, ACLEDS
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <a
              href="/team"
              class="btn btn-outline btn-sm"
              style="width:100%; justify-content:center; margin-top:1.25rem"
              >View Team</a
            >
          </div>
        </aside>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .page-hero {
    padding: 5rem 0 4rem;
  }
  .page-hero h1 {
    color: var(--white);
    margin: 0.75rem 0 0.5rem;
    font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 4vw, 3rem);
  }
  .page-hero-sub {
    color: rgba(232, 237, 244, 0.7);
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    max-width: 64ch;
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  .back-link {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.35rem;
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    color: rgba(232, 237, 244, 0.5);
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    transition: color var(--transition);
  }
  .back-link:hover {
    color: var(--gold);
  }

  .hero-tags {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .project-mono {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    color: var(--gold);
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .project-status {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.68rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    padding: 0.2rem 0.6rem;
    border-radius: 2px;
  }
  .project-status.active {
    background: rgba(34, 197, 94, 0.15);
    color: #4ade80;
  }

  /* Facts bar */
  .facts-bar {
    background: var(--navy-mid);
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(200, 151, 58, 0.1);
  }
  .facts-inner {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0;
    padding-top: 0;
    padding-bottom: 0;
  }
  .fact-item {
    flex: 1;
    min-width: 140px;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.2rem;
  }
  .fact-label {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.65rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--gold);
  }
  .fact-val {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: rgba(232, 237, 244, 0.85);
    font-weight: 500;
  }
  .fact-divider {
    width: 1px;
    height: 36px;
    background: rgba(200, 151, 58, 0.12);
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  /* Layout */
  .project-layout {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 300px;
    gap: 3.5rem;
    align-items: start;
  }

  .project-body {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 3.5rem;
  }
  .body-section p {
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }
  .body-section h2 {
    margin-top: 0.4rem;
  }

  /* RQ list */
  .rq-list {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    margin-top: 1rem;
    list-style: none;
  }
  .rq-list li {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1.25rem;
    align-items: flex-start;
  }
  .rq-num {
    flex-shrink: 0;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.68rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--gold);
    background: rgba(200, 151, 58, 0.1);
    padding: 0.2rem 0.5rem;
    border-radius: 2px;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    margin-top: 2px;
  }
  .rq-list strong {
    display: block;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.3rem;
  }
  .rq-list p {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* Methods */
  .method-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(220px, 1fr));
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-top: 1.25rem;
  }
  .method-card {
    padding: 1.25rem;
    background: var(--fog);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--gold);
  }
  .method-card h4 {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
  }
  .method-card p {
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* Implications */
  .implications-list {
    margin-top: 1rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.65rem;
  }
  .implications-list li {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
    position: relative;
  }
  .implications-list li::before {
    content: "";
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    top: 0.55em;
    width: 5px;
    height: 5px;
    background: var(--gold);
    border-radius: 50%;
  }

  /* Sidebar */
  .sidebar-card {
    padding: 1.5rem;
  }
  .sidebar-pubs {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-top: 0.75rem;
  }
  .sidebar-pub {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.35rem;
  }
  .sidebar-pub p {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    line-height: 1.45;
  }
  .pub-author {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
  }
  .pub-link-sm {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--gold);
  }

  .pi-block {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.85rem;
    margin-top: 0.85rem;
  }
  .pi-avatar {
    width: 44px;
    height: 44px;
    background: rgba(200, 151, 58, 0.15);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    display: grid;
    place-items: center;
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--gold);
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .project-layout {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
    .project-sidebar {
      order: -1;
    }
    .facts-inner {
      gap: 0;
    }
    .fact-divider {
      display: none;
    }
    .fact-item {
      min-width: calc(50% - 0.5rem);
      border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(200, 151, 58, 0.08);
    }
  }
</style>
